explanation:
When wait() is called on a thread, it needs to be in a synchronized block. As we haven't used wait() within synchronized block, we get IllegalMonitorStateException.

The correct code is
public void run() {

for(int i=0;i<10;i++) {
synchronized(this) {
try {

this.wait(100);
} catch (InterruptedException e) {
	e.printStackTrace();
}
System.out.println("Hi I am runnable"+i);
}
}
}

